body.description: Powerful drivers for excellent-quality audio Hi-Fi sound quality These 2-pack wired ear buds design for iPhone, come with a clear microphone and an ergonomic comfortable-fit design, combining powerful bass and dynamic stereo sound. Enjoy your music to the fullest with large, 9mm drivers for crystal-clear highs and deep, impactful lows. Combining a wide frequency response range of 12Hz – 23kHz, 200mW maximum input power and 96B/mW sensitivity, these powerful earbuds ensure you’ll hear every detail in your favorite tunes, from the crisp strings of classical music, to the powerful bass beats of pop and hip hop.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars They require Bluetooth
reviews.reviewText: These are even crappier than I expected. They require Bluetooth connectivity to operate and the sound is absolutely horrible. They cannot operate within the full sound range of the phone. I’d recommend spend another 5-10 bucks for another brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I use the wire version to listen to my music. Not a fan of earbuds.These speakers are high quality, they come in a pair, just in case you lose them, and they are inexpensive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are absolutely terrible. Leaving aside the fact that wired earbuds which require Bluetooth make no sense at all, both pairs in the two pack were pretty much unusable within a week. One pair lost all sound in the right side, the other fades in and out constantly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Get what you pay for
reviews.reviewText: They’re cheaply made. The first pair stopped working properly within 2 weeks. They also connect as “baets” which I’m assuming is supposed to look like “beats” but also the entire point in having wired headphones is so that you’re not using wireless headphones. I don’t know why the phone reads them as wireless headphones, but it does. I’ve bought two packs of cheap headphones before and they were not this bad. Wouldn’t recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Wired but still bluetooth
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these because I wanted non-bluetooth headphones, only to find out these are wired but still require bluetooth in order to connect. The connection is also very temperamental and doesn't always connect on the first try (or second or third). The volume is either too low or too high and you can't get it to go in the middle. Sound quality is good but nothing that any other pair of headphones could give.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars JUNK - DO NOT WORK AT ALL
reviews.reviewText: They don’t work at all - they are junk - waste of time and money and now I get to package and send them back spending more time and money - don’t waste your time or money on these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Sound is ok, but mic is not as good as an apple product
reviews.reviewText: In order to use these headphones with an iPhone, you have to select Connect each time. The sound quality is as good as my Apple headphones, but my friends have told me it's harder to hear me when using them compared to my Apple headphones.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not as advertised
reviews.reviewText: The headphones are loud. I’ll give it that however, they are supposed to be a microphone as well. There’s even a picture of a microphone on the mouthpiece. It doesn’t work, neither pair. It acts like a Bluetooth but it’s not. I don’t know how to explain it I plugged the headphones into my phone and they connected to my business phone, which was right next to it, and I could hear things off my business phone while I was plugged into my personal phone. It was weird both headphones did the exact same thing, I’m going to Apple and I’m purchasing a real pair for the same. These are supposed to be plain wired headphones, not Bluetooth but as long as it’s plugged into a power source, it will Bluetooth so weird.
